Title: Code and Community with RenderATL
Description: From Universe, Andrea talks with Justin “ThugDebugger” Samuels (Mailchimp, founder of RenderATL) about building welcoming, culture-first tech conferences. Justin shares RenderATL’s growth from 300 to 8,000 attendees, its volunteer-driven community, and a reported $55M economic impact in FY2025 across related events. He announces RenderATL is moving to August 12–13 due to the FIFA World Cup in Atlanta, and introduces The Commits, a black-tie, high-production open source awards show with nominations open until around April/May and winners selected by a committee of open source maintainers.
